1
00:00:04,760 --> 00:00:05,360
Wendy,

2
00:00:05,440 --> 00:00:07,000
are you free today?

3
00:00:07,400 --> 00:00:08,000
Just go.

4
00:00:08,200 --> 00:00:09,600
Don't keep me from making money.

5
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:10,640
I brought this for you.

6
00:00:10,640 --> 00:00:11,200
I don't want it.

7
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:11,930
Take it away.

8
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:13,640
Alright.

9
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:22,080
Wendy.

10
00:00:22,920 --> 00:00:25,840
That guy just now seems like a good catch,

11
00:00:26,080 --> 00:00:27,880
and he comes to see you every day.

12
00:00:27,920 --> 00:00:29,980
Are you really just sending him away?

13
00:00:30,720 --> 00:00:31,280
Shasha.

14
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:34,930
Even though I'm so popular with men right now,

15
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:36,280
my life in the past

16
00:00:36,280 --> 00:00:37,610
wasn't like this at all.

17
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:39,660
Back then, everyone hated me.

18
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:40,920
No one liked me.

19
00:00:58,400 --> 00:00:59,440
Come here.

20
00:01:11,200 --> 00:01:12,460
This is me from before.

21
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,200
Is this really you?

22
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:23,610
You've changed so much.

23
00:01:23,840 --> 00:01:24,800
Of course.

24
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:27,400
You have no idea what it took to become like this,

25
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:28,440
how much I suffered,

26
00:01:28,440 --> 00:01:29,900
and how much money I spent.

27
00:01:30,440 --> 00:01:31,800
That guy just now,

28
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:35,600
I actually used to like him a lot.

29
00:01:35,680 --> 00:01:37,410
But he wouldn't even look at me.

30
00:01:38,080 --> 00:01:38,880
And now?

31
00:01:38,880 --> 00:01:40,600
He's dying to talk to me.

32
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:42,740
He doesn't like me for who I am.

33
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:45,800
He just likes my current appearance.

34
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:47,660
Ever since I got plastic surgery,

35
00:01:48,479 --> 00:01:49,680
no one recognizes me.

36
00:01:51,320 --> 00:01:54,180
I can finally say goodbye to everything in the past.

37
00:02:02,320 --> 00:02:03,120
Lin Wei.

38
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:06,540
Captain Li.

39
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:08,759
You'll take Ma Guodong's seat from now on.

40
00:02:08,759 --> 00:02:10,440
This is only a temporary arrangement.

41
00:02:10,440 --> 00:02:11,840
We'll see about Ma later.

42
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:14,200
Why?

43
00:02:14,520 --> 00:02:15,400
We have new recruits in the team.

44
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:17,060
You have to train at least one.

45
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:18,000
She'll sit here.

46
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,200
And you'll sit there.

47
00:02:19,440 --> 00:02:20,880
Captain Li, I'd rather not.

48
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:22,140
You know my situation.

49
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:27,200
That person was transferred from Chudong.

50
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:29,000
They specifically asked to follow you.

51
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:29,920
What can I do?

52
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:30,720
Who is it?

53
00:02:32,640 --> 00:02:33,370
Captain Lin.

54
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:48,079
Shasha.

55
00:02:49,880 --> 00:02:51,040
Where are you?

56
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:53,600
Wendy.

57
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:55,160
What's wrong?

58
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:56,280
Did you drink?

59
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:56,960
I did.

60
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:58,600
I'm happy.

61
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:05,080
I have good news for you.

62
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:07,560
What is it?

63
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:11,540
Didn't you want to open a flower shop?

64
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,890
I'm giving this shop to you.

65
00:03:14,880 --> 00:03:15,540
From now on,

66
00:03:16,640 --> 00:03:18,600
you are the boss of this flower shop.

67
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:19,960
You've had too much to drink.

68
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:21,160
Are you serious?

69
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:24,280
I'm very serious.

70
00:03:26,079 --> 00:03:27,880
But I don't have that much money.

71
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:32,210
Just give me whatever you have.

72
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:34,280
Because I've

73
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:36,079
found my true love.

74
00:03:37,079 --> 00:03:38,160
I'm going

75
00:03:38,920 --> 00:03:40,760
abroad with him soon

76
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:42,480
to embrace my new life.

77
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:50,200
Well,

78
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:51,700
congratulations.

79
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:55,200
Hand.

80
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,080
Give me a hug.

81
00:04:10,480 --> 00:04:13,280
I don't know when we'll see each other again.

82
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:19,000
Shasha.

83
00:04:20,399 --> 00:04:22,330
You will embrace your new life too.

84
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:24,480
I wish you happiness.

85
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:27,080
I will.

86
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:29,740
I definitely will.

87
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:45,200
Excuse me.

88
00:04:45,880 --> 00:04:48,010
Which flowers are the freshest today?

89
00:04:52,159 --> 00:04:54,120
What kind of flowers would you like to buy, sir?

90
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:56,880
Sir, these flowers just arrived today.

91
00:04:57,320 --> 00:04:59,580
Why don't you take a look over here first?

92
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:04,620
What are you afraid of?

93
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:07,610
Go back inside and get back to work.

94
00:05:15,080 --> 00:05:16,480
Call her sister-in-law.

95
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:19,090
Sister-in-law.

96
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:24,690
Have you heard about the ID card replacement?

97
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:27,520
Aren't you worried you can't hide anymore?

98
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:30,280
Not bad.

99
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:32,640
You're a boss now.

100
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:36,200
Must be making a lot of money, right?

101
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:38,409
What exactly do you want to say?

102
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:41,159
With such a good life,

103
00:05:41,159 --> 00:05:42,159
you wouldn't want

104
00:05:42,840 --> 00:05:45,300
a threat like me around in the future, right?

105
00:05:46,159 --> 00:05:47,280
I mean to say,

106
00:05:48,880 --> 00:05:51,080
it's time we settled things between us.

107
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:52,050
Don't you think?

108
00:05:53,840 --> 00:05:56,240
I've given you a lot of money this past year.

109
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:58,290
I stopped owing you a long time ago.

110
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:00,460
It's not me you owe.

111
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:02,600
It's my older brother.

112
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:05,000
Fine.

113
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:06,600
You don't have to give it to me.

114
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:08,080
We can go to the police station

115
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:09,720
and chat with the folks inside

116
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:11,120
about our story.

117
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:13,080
If they don't believe us,

118
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:14,880
we can

119
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:16,680
go find my brother together.

120
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:18,760
The person my brother loved the most

121
00:06:18,760 --> 00:06:19,890
has always been you.

122
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:21,480
He must miss you a lot.

123
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:24,400
This is the last time.

124
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:27,330
Don't bother me ever again.

125
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:29,520
Name a price.

126
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:33,530
How much do you have?

127
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:35,320
I'll take whatever you have.

128
00:06:41,080 --> 00:06:42,240
He will come to you.

129
00:06:45,080 --> 00:06:46,000
Shasha.

130
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,080
That man just now was so fierce.

131
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:48,080
Do you know him?

132
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:49,130
I don't know him.

133
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:50,930
He just came to buy flowers.

134
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:52,850
But he didn't buy any in the end.

135
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:57,920
Shasha.

136
00:06:58,520 --> 00:07:01,120
That man named Deng came looking for you again.

137
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:03,600
Go inside first.

138
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:12,480
Shasha, these are flowers for you.

139
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:13,480
Do you like them?

140
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:15,280
No.

141
00:07:15,280 --> 00:07:16,120
Why?

142
00:07:16,320 --> 00:07:17,850
Don't you run a flower shop?

143
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:20,160
It's not that I don't like flowers.

144
00:07:20,760 --> 00:07:21,960
I just don't like you.

145
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:27,360
Shasha, you know my feelings for you are real.

146
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:28,220
I don't need it.

147
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:30,290
And I don't want to get married.

148
00:07:30,760 --> 00:07:33,240
Don't waste your time on me anymore.

149
00:07:54,760 --> 00:07:55,720
You followed me.

150
00:07:56,520 --> 00:07:57,840
What do you mean?

151
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:00,520
I've been at your flower shop for two days.

152
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:01,560
It's been closed.

153
00:08:01,760 --> 00:08:03,560
Do you not want the shop anymore?

154
00:08:04,880 --> 00:08:06,610
A dignified flower shop owner,

155
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:08,720
staying in such a crappy hotel.

156
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:10,380
What kind of standard is this?

157
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:13,540
How long are you going to hide from me?

158
00:08:13,760 --> 00:08:15,420
Where is the money I asked for?

159
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,260
I don't have any money.

160
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:21,210
If you don't have money, go sell yourself.

161
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:23,080
Back when you hung out with us,

162
00:08:23,280 --> 00:08:25,740
didn't you always rely on selling yourself?

163
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,130
How much do you want?

164
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:30,160
Name a price.

165
00:08:35,760 --> 00:08:37,289
I'm leaving here tomorrow.

166
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:38,320
200,000.

167
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:40,090
I want it now.

168
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:48,060
I don't have that much on me right now.

169
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:52,280
Give me a day.

170
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:55,210
I'll find a way to get the money for you.

171
00:09:25,880 --> 00:09:26,680
Alright.

172
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:28,520
I'll give you one day.

173
00:09:29,720 --> 00:09:31,180
Tomorrow night at 9:00 PM.

174
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:33,020
Meet me at the pier warehouse.

175
00:09:35,520 --> 00:09:36,320
Deal.

176
00:09:41,920 --> 00:09:42,880
Don't touch me.

177
00:09:47,160 --> 00:09:49,020
If I don't see the money tomorrow,

178
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:51,610
I'm not going anywhere.

179
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:52,760
I'll take you

180
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:55,060
to the police station with me.

181
00:09:55,680 --> 00:09:56,360
Bye.

182
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:58,920
My dear sister-in-law.

183
00:10:26,760 --> 00:10:28,280
What time was our appointment?

184
00:10:28,280 --> 00:10:29,480
The boat is about to leave.

185
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:31,340
Doesn't raising money take time?

186
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:32,980
Where's the money?

187
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:35,520
It's all here.

188
00:10:35,680 --> 00:10:36,740
Count it yourself.

189
00:10:36,920 --> 00:10:38,680
I can't let you go if it's even one cent short.
